Police want to be granted 14 days to complete investigations and continue detaining a woman who fled Dubai after allegedly stealing Sh140 million. Rebecca Musau was arrested on Tuesday night at the Namanga border control as she tried to cross to Tanzania. Detective Emmanuel Ngetich said that on May 15, Inspector General of Police received a letter from the Foreign Affairs ministry that Musau, together with others not before court, left Dubai on March 4 with Sh140 million stolen money. The court heard that they stole the money from a car in transit belonging to a company named Transuard. It was destined to refill an ATM at Dierra City Mall in Dubai, the United Arab Emirates. The court is to rule on the application today. Read: Woman accused of Sh137m theft seized in Namanga Click here for
the latest political news